biochemistry, including heterogeneous catalysis, where it
is often used to rationalize observed variations in catalytic
activity from one catalyst to the next or to estimate ac-
tivation barriers (3). There is little quantitative evidence
behind the BrnstedEvansPolanyi relation in heteroge-
neouscatalysis,becauseitishardtomeasurebothactivation
energies and reaction energies (or rates and equilibrium
